# Instinct RPG — Primer card render parity

The primer does **not** load Card Studio’s full card CSS from `index.html`. It loads only
`primer-card-scope.css` + `instinct-dual-styles.css`. Any gap here shows up as broken or overflowing
cards in chargen samples (e.g. Core `.card-body` templates).

## Template checklist

When card HTML changes in Baserow or `card-data.js`, verify scoped styles exist for every body
template used in primer samples:

| Template | Body class | Required scoped selectors |
|----------|------------|---------------------------|
| Ability / Act / React | `.cbody` | `.flv`, `.etxt`, `.elbl`, `.csec`, `.clbl`, `.crow`, `.ci` |
| Bond / Instinct / Connection forks | `.bf-body` | `.bf-trig`, `.bf-eff`, `.bf-choose`, etc. + `instinct-dual-styles.css` |
| Core | `.card-body` | `.zone-label`, `.effect-text`, `.rule` |
| Oath / special Core layouts | `.card-body` + custom | `.vow-grid`, `.vow-phrase`, `.vow-ix`, `.die-target`, `.vow-the-ring`, `.effect-text`, `.rule` — see `instinct-core-card-design.mdc` |

Shared rules already in `primer-card-scope.css`:

- `.card` — `2.5in × 3.5in`, flex column, `overflow: hidden`
- Body regions — `padding-bottom: 26px` to clear absolute `.idtag`
- `.cardwrap` — `scale(0.58)`, `transform-origin: top left`

## Layout rule — one scaled card per slot

```html
<!-- Correct: one card per .primer-cards -->
<div class="primer-cards"><div id="some-wrap"></div></div>

<!-- Correct: side-by-side Core pair -->
<div class="primer-core-pair">
  <div class="primer-cards"><div id="core-a"></div></div>
  <div class="primer-cards"><div id="core-b"></div></div>
</div>

<!-- Wrong: two cardwraps inside one .primer-cards without .primer-core-pair -->
```

Never stack two mounted cards in a single `.primer-cards` container — negative margins and scale
transforms are tuned for **one** card per slot.

## Agent workflow after template changes

1. Identify which `Card_Key` samples use the new/changed HTML shape.
2. Add or update rules under `.primer-cards …` in `primer-card-scope.css`.
3. Open the live primer (or local `instinct-rpg-primer-v2.html`) and visually confirm **every**
   chargen sample — especially Core, Bond forks, and longest text cards.
4. Commit + push per `instinct-git.mdc`.

